{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I'm going to try and do in the next 15 minutes or so"},{"time":3000,"text":"is tell you about an idea"},{"time":5000,"text":"of how we're going to make matter come alive."},{"time":8000,"text":"Now this may seem a bit ambitious,"},{"time":10000,"text":"but when you look at yourself, you look at your hands,"},{"time":12000,"text":"you realize that you're alive."},{"time":14000,"text":"So this is a start."},{"time":16000,"text":"Now this quest started four billion years ago on planet Earth."},{"time":19000,"text":"There's been four billion years"},{"time":21000,"text":"of organic, biological life."},{"time":23000,"text":"And as an inorganic chemist,"},{"time":25000,"text":"my friends and colleagues make this distinction"},{"time":27000,"text":"between the organic, living world"},{"time":30000,"text":"and the inorganic, dead world."},{"time":32000,"text":"And what I'm going to try and do is plant some ideas"},{"time":35000,"text":"about how we can transform inorganic, dead matter"},{"time":39000,"text":"into living matter, into inorganic biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Before we do that,"},{"time":44000,"text":"I want to kind of put biology in its place."},{"time":47000,"text":"And I'm absolutely enthralled by biology."},{"time":49000,"text":"I love to do synthetic biology."},{"time":51000,"text":"I love things that are alive."},{"time":53000,"text":"I love manipulating the infrastructure of biology."},{"time":55000,"text":"But within that infrastructure,"},{"time":57000,"text":"we have to remember"},{"time":59000,"text":"that the driving force of biology"},{"time":61000,"text":"is really coming from evolution."},{"time":63000,"text":"And evolution,"},{"time":65000,"text":"although it was established well over 100 years ago by Charles Darwin"},{"time":68000,"text":"and a vast number of other people,"},{"time":70000,"text":"evolution still is a little bit intangible."},{"time":73000,"text":"And when I talk about Darwinian evolution,"},{"time":75000,"text":"I mean one thing and one thing only,"},{"time":77000,"text":"and that is survival of the fittest."},{"time":79000,"text":"And so forget about evolution"},{"time":81000,"text":"in a kind of metaphysical way."},{"time":83000,"text":"Think about evolution"},{"time":85000,"text":"in terms of offspring competing,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and some winning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"So bearing that in mind,"},{"time":91000,"text":"as a chemist, I wanted to ask myself"},{"time":93000,"text":"the question frustrated by biology:"},{"time":95000,"text":"What is the minimal unit of matter"},{"time":98000,"text":"that can undergo Darwinian evolution?"},{"time":101000,"text":"And this seems quite a profound question."},{"time":103000,"text":"And as a chemist,"},{"time":105000,"text":"we're not used to profound questions every day."},{"time":107000,"text":"So when I thought about it,"},{"time":109000,"text":"then suddenly I realized"},{"time":111000,"text":"that biology gave us the answer."},{"time":113000,"text":"And in fact, the smallest unit of matter"},{"time":115000,"text":"that can evolve independently"},{"time":117000,"text":"is, in fact, a single cell --"},{"time":119000,"text":"a bacteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"So this raises three really important questions:"},{"time":124000,"text":"What is life?"},{"time":126000,"text":"Is biology special?"},{"time":128000,"text":"Biologists seem to think so."},{"time":130000,"text":"Is matter evolvable?"},{"time":132000,"text":"Now if we answer those questions in reverse order,"},{"time":135000,"text":"the third question -- is matter evolvable? --"},{"time":137000,"text":"if we can answer that,"},{"time":139000,"text":"then we're going to know how special biology is,"},{"time":141000,"text":"and maybe, just maybe,"},{"time":143000,"text":"we'll have some idea of what life really is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"So here's some inorganic life."},{"time":148000,"text":"This is a dead crystal,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and I'm going to do something to it,"},{"time":152000,"text":"and it's going to become alive."},{"time":154000,"text":"And you can see,"},{"time":156000,"text":"it's kind of pollinating, germinating, growing."},{"time":159000,"text":"This is an inorganic tube."},{"time":161000,"text":"And all these crystals here under the microscope"},{"time":163000,"text":"were dead a few minutes ago, and they look alive."},{"time":165000,"text":"Of course, they're not alive."},{"time":167000,"text":"It's a chemistry experiment where I've made a crystal garden."},{"time":170000,"text":"But when I saw this, I was really fascinated,"},{"time":173000,"text":"because it seemed lifelike."},{"time":175000,"text":"And as I pause for a few seconds, have a look at the screen."},{"time":180000,"text":"You can see there's architecture growing, filling the void."},{"time":183000,"text":"And this is dead."},{"time":185000,"text":"So I was positive that,"},{"time":187000,"text":"if somehow we can make things mimic life,"},{"time":189000,"text":"let's go one step further."},{"time":191000,"text":"Let's see if we can actually make life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"But there's a problem,"},{"time":195000,"text":"because up until maybe a decade ago,"},{"time":197000,"text":"we were told that life was impossible"},{"time":199000,"text":"and that we were the most incredible miracle in the universe."},{"time":202000,"text":"In fact, we were the only people"},{"time":204000,"text":"in the universe."},{"time":206000,"text":"Now, that's a bit boring."},{"time":208000,"text":"So as a chemist,"},{"time":210000,"text":"I wanted to say, \"Hang on. What is going on here?"},{"time":212000,"text":"Is life that improbable?\""},{"time":214000,"text":"And this is really the question."},{"time":217000,"text":"I think that perhaps the emergence of the first cells"},{"time":220000,"text":"was as probable as the emergence of the stars."},{"time":223000,"text":"And in fact, let's take that one step further."},{"time":226000,"text":"Let's say"},{"time":228000,"text":"that if the physics of fusion"},{"time":230000,"text":"is encoded into the universe,"},{"time":232000,"text":"maybe the physics of life is as well."},{"time":234000,"text":"And so the problem with chemists --"},{"time":236000,"text":"and this is a massive advantage as well --"},{"time":238000,"text":"is we like to focus on our elements."},{"time":240000,"text":"In biology, carbon takes center stage."},{"time":243000,"text":"And in a universe where carbon exists"},{"time":245000,"text":"and organic biology,"},{"time":247000,"text":"then we have all this wonderful diversity of life."},{"time":250000,"text":"In fact, we have such amazing lifeforms that we can manipulate."},{"time":254000,"text":"We're awfully careful in the lab"},{"time":256000,"text":"to try and avoid various biohazards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"Well what about matter?"},{"time":260000,"text":"If we can make matter alive, would we have a matterhazard?"},{"time":263000,"text":"So think, this is a serious question."},{"time":265000,"text":"If your pen could replicate,"},{"time":268000,"text":"that would be a bit of a problem."},{"time":270000,"text":"So we have to think differently"},{"time":272000,"text":"if we're going to make stuff come alive."},{"time":274000,"text":"And we also have to be aware of the issues."},{"time":276000,"text":"But before we can make life,"},{"time":278000,"text":"let's think for a second"},{"time":280000,"text":"what life really is characterized by."},{"time":282000,"text":"And forgive the complicated diagram."},{"time":284000,"text":"This is just a collection of pathways in the cell."},{"time":287000,"text":"And the cell is obviously for us"},{"time":289000,"text":"a fascinating thing."},{"time":291000,"text":"Synthetic biologists are manipulating it."},{"time":294000,"text":"Chemists are trying to study the molecules to look at disease."},{"time":297000,"text":"And you have all these pathways going on at the same time."},{"time":299000,"text":"You have regulation;"},{"time":301000,"text":"information is transcribed;"},{"time":303000,"text":"catalysts are made; stuff is happening."},{"time":305000,"text":"But what does a cell do?"},{"time":307000,"text":"Well it divides, it competes,"},{"time":309000,"text":"it survives."},{"time":311000,"text":"And I think that is where we have to start"},{"time":313000,"text":"in terms of thinking about"},{"time":315000,"text":"building from our ideas in life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"But what else is life characterized by?"},{"time":319000,"text":"Well, I like think of it"},{"time":321000,"text":"as a flame in a bottle."},{"time":323000,"text":"And so what we have here"},{"time":325000,"text":"is a description of single cells"},{"time":327000,"text":"replicating, metabolizing,"},{"time":329000,"text":"burning through chemistries."},{"time":331000,"text":"And so we have to understand"},{"time":333000,"text":"that if we're going to make artificial life or understand the origin of life,"},{"time":336000,"text":"we need to power it somehow."},{"time":338000,"text":"So before we can really start to make life,"},{"time":341000,"text":"we have to really think about where it came from."},{"time":343000,"text":"And Darwin himself mused in a letter to a colleague"},{"time":345000,"text":"that he thought that life probably emerged"},{"time":347000,"text":"in some warm little pond somewhere --"},{"time":350000,"text":"maybe not in Scotland, maybe in Africa,"},{"time":352000,"text":"maybe somewhere else."},{"time":354000,"text":"But the real honest answer is, we just don't know,"},{"time":357000,"text":"because there is a problem with the origin."},{"time":360000,"text":"Imagine way back, four and a half billion years ago,"},{"time":363000,"text":"there is a vast chemical soup of stuff."},{"time":365000,"text":"And from this stuff we came."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"So when you think about the improbable nature"},{"time":370000,"text":"of what I'm going to tell you in the next few minutes,"},{"time":372000,"text":"just remember,"},{"time":374000,"text":"we came from stuff on planet Earth."},{"time":376000,"text":"And we went through a variety of worlds."},{"time":379000,"text":"The RNA people would talk about the RNA world."},{"time":382000,"text":"We somehow got to proteins and DNA."},{"time":384000,"text":"We then got to the last ancestor."},{"time":386000,"text":"Evolution kicked in -- and that's the cool bit."},{"time":389000,"text":"And here we are."},{"time":391000,"text":"But there's a roadblock that you can't get past."},{"time":394000,"text":"You can decode the genome, you can look back,"},{"time":397000,"text":"you can link us all together by a mitochondrial DNA,"},{"time":400000,"text":"but we can't get further than the last ancestor,"},{"time":403000,"text":"the last visible cell"},{"time":405000,"text":"that we could sequence or think back in history."},{"time":408000,"text":"So we don't know how we got here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"So there are two options:"},{"time":413000,"text":"intelligent design, direct and indirect --"},{"time":415000,"text":"so God,"},{"time":417000,"text":"or my friend."},{"time":420000,"text":"Now talking about E.T. putting us there, or some other life,"},{"time":423000,"text":"just pushes the problem further on."},{"time":426000,"text":"I'm not a politician, I'm a scientist."},{"time":429000,"text":"The other thing we need to think about"},{"time":431000,"text":"is the emergence of chemical complexity."},{"time":433000,"text":"This seems most likely."},{"time":435000,"text":"So we have some kind of primordial soup."},{"time":437000,"text":"And this one happens to be"},{"time":439000,"text":"a good source of all 20 amino acids."},{"time":441000,"text":"And somehow"},{"time":443000,"text":"these amino acids are combined,"},{"time":445000,"text":"and life begins."},{"time":447000,"text":"But life begins, what does that mean?"},{"time":449000,"text":"What is life? What is this stuff of life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452000,"text":"So in the 1950s,"},{"time":454000,"text":"Miller-Urey did their fantastic chemical Frankenstein experiment,"},{"time":459000,"text":"where they did the equivalent in the chemical world."},{"time":461000,"text":"They took the basic ingredients, put them in a single jar"},{"time":464000,"text":"and ignited them"},{"time":466000,"text":"and put a lot of voltage through."},{"time":468000,"text":"And they had a look at what was in the soup,"},{"time":470000,"text":"and they found amino acids,"},{"time":473000,"text":"but nothing came out, there was no cell."},{"time":475000,"text":"So the whole area's been stuck for a while,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and it got reignited in the '80s"},{"time":481000,"text":"when analytical technologies and computer technologies were coming on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"In my own laboratory,"},{"time":486000,"text":"the way we're trying to create inorganic life"},{"time":489000,"text":"is by using many different reaction formats."},{"time":491000,"text":"So what we're trying to do is do reactions --"},{"time":493000,"text":"not in one flask, but in tens of flasks,"},{"time":495000,"text":"and connect them together,"},{"time":497000,"text":"as you can see with this flow system, all these pipes."},{"time":499000,"text":"We can do it microfluidically, we can do it lithographically,"},{"time":502000,"text":"we can do it in a 3D printer,"},{"time":504000,"text":"we can do it in droplets for colleagues."},{"time":506000,"text":"And the key thing is to have lots of complex chemistry"},{"time":509000,"text":"just bubbling away."},{"time":511000,"text":"But that's probably going to end in failure,"},{"time":515000,"text":"so we need to be a bit more focused."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"And the answer, of course, lies with mice."},{"time":519000,"text":"This is how I remember what I need as a chemist."},{"time":522000,"text":"I say, \"Well I want molecules.\""},{"time":524000,"text":"But I need a metabolism, I need some energy."},{"time":527000,"text":"I need some information, and I need a container."},{"time":530000,"text":"Because if I want evolution,"},{"time":532000,"text":"I need containers to compete."},{"time":534000,"text":"So if you have a container,"},{"time":536000,"text":"it's like getting in your car."},{"time":538000,"text":"\"This is my car,"},{"time":540000,"text":"and I'm going to drive around and show off my car.\""},{"time":542000,"text":"And I imagine you have a similar thing"},{"time":544000,"text":"in cellular biology"},{"time":546000,"text":"with the emergence of life."},{"time":548000,"text":"So these things together give us evolution, perhaps."},{"time":551000,"text":"And the way to test it in the laboratory"},{"time":553000,"text":"is to make it minimal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555000,"text":"So what we're going to try and do"},{"time":557000,"text":"is come up with an inorganic Lego kit of molecules."},{"time":560000,"text":"And so forgive the molecules on the screen,"},{"time":562000,"text":"but these are a very simple kit."},{"time":564000,"text":"There's only maybe three or four different types of building blocks present."},{"time":566000,"text":"And we can aggregate them together"},{"time":568000,"text":"and make literally thousands and thousands"},{"time":570000,"text":"of really big nano-molecular molecules"},{"time":573000,"text":"the same size of DNA and proteins,"},{"time":575000,"text":"but there's no carbon in sight."},{"time":577000,"text":"Carbon is banned."},{"time":579000,"text":"And so with this Lego kit,"},{"time":581000,"text":"we have the diversity required"},{"time":583000,"text":"for complex information storage"},{"time":586000,"text":"without DNA."},{"time":588000,"text":"But we need to make some containers."},{"time":590000,"text":"And just a few months ago in my lab,"},{"time":592000,"text":"we were able to take these very same molecules and make cells with them."},{"time":595000,"text":"And you can see on the screen a cell being made."},{"time":598000,"text":"And we're now going to put some chemistry inside and do some chemistry in this cell."},{"time":601000,"text":"And all I wanted to show you"},{"time":603000,"text":"is we can set up molecules"},{"time":605000,"text":"in membranes, in real cells,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and then it sets up a kind of molecular Darwinism,"},{"time":611000,"text":"a molecular survival of the fittest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"And this movie here"},{"time":615000,"text":"shows this competition between molecules."},{"time":617000,"text":"Molecules are competing for stuff."},{"time":619000,"text":"They're all made of the same stuff,"},{"time":621000,"text":"but they want their shape to win."},{"time":623000,"text":"They want their shape to persist."},{"time":625000,"text":"And that is the key."},{"time":627000,"text":"If we can somehow encourage these molecules"},{"time":629000,"text":"to talk to each other and make the right shapes and compete,"},{"time":632000,"text":"they will start to form cells"},{"time":634000,"text":"that will replicate and compete."},{"time":636000,"text":"If we manage to do that,"},{"time":638000,"text":"forget the molecular detail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641000,"text":"Let's zoom out to what that could mean."},{"time":643000,"text":"So we have this special theory of evolution"},{"time":645000,"text":"that applies only to organic biology, to us."},{"time":648000,"text":"If we could get evolution into the material world,"},{"time":651000,"text":"then I propose we should have a general theory of evolution."},{"time":654000,"text":"And that's really worth thinking about."},{"time":657000,"text":"Does evolution control"},{"time":659000,"text":"the sophistication of matter in the universe?"},{"time":662000,"text":"Is there some driving force through evolution"},{"time":665000,"text":"that allows matter to compete?"},{"time":667000,"text":"So that means we could then start"},{"time":669000,"text":"to develop different platforms"},{"time":672000,"text":"for exploring this evolution."},{"time":674000,"text":"So you imagine,"},{"time":676000,"text":"if we're able to create a self-sustaining artificial life form,"},{"time":679000,"text":"not only will this tell us about the origin of life --"},{"time":682000,"text":"that it's possible that the universe doesn't need carbon to be alive;"},{"time":685000,"text":"it can use anything --"},{"time":687000,"text":"we can then take [it] one step further and develop new technologies,"},{"time":690000,"text":"because we can then use software control"},{"time":692000,"text":"for evolution to code in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694000,"text":"So imagine we make a little cell."},{"time":696000,"text":"We want to put it out in the environment,"},{"time":698000,"text":"and we want it to be powered by the Sun."},{"time":700000,"text":"What we do is we evolve it in a box with a light on."},{"time":703000,"text":"And we don't use design anymore. We find what works."},{"time":706000,"text":"We should take our inspiration from biology."},{"time":708000,"text":"Biology doesn't care about the design"},{"time":710000,"text":"unless it works."},{"time":712000,"text":"So this will reorganize"},{"time":714000,"text":"the way we design things."},{"time":716000,"text":"But not only just that,"},{"time":718000,"text":"we will start to think about"},{"time":720000,"text":"how we can start to develop a symbiotic relationship with biology."},{"time":723000,"text":"Wouldn't it be great"},{"time":725000,"text":"if you could take these artificial biological cells"},{"time":727000,"text":"and fuse them with biological ones"},{"time":729000,"text":"to correct problems that we couldn't really deal with?"},{"time":732000,"text":"The real issue in cellular biology"},{"time":734000,"text":"is we are never going to understand everything,"},{"time":737000,"text":"because it's a multidimensional problem put there by evolution."},{"time":740000,"text":"Evolution cannot be cut apart."},{"time":743000,"text":"You need to somehow find the fitness function."},{"time":746000,"text":"And the profound realization for me"},{"time":748000,"text":"is that, if this works,"},{"time":750000,"text":"the concept of the selfish gene gets kicked up a level,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and we really start talking about selfish matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"And what does that mean in a universe"},{"time":758000,"text":"where we are right now the highest form of stuff?"},{"time":761000,"text":"You're sitting on chairs."},{"time":763000,"text":"They're inanimate, they're not alive."},{"time":765000,"text":"But you are made of stuff, and you are using stuff,"},{"time":767000,"text":"and you enslave stuff."},{"time":769000,"text":"So using evolution"},{"time":771000,"text":"in biology,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and in inorganic biology,"},{"time":775000,"text":"for me is quite appealing, quite exciting."},{"time":777000,"text":"And we're really becoming very close"},{"time":780000,"text":"to understanding the key steps"},{"time":782000,"text":"that makes dead stuff come alive."},{"time":785000,"text":"And again, when you're thinking about how improbable this is,"},{"time":788000,"text":"remember, five billion years ago,"},{"time":790000,"text":"we were not here, and there was no life."},{"time":793000,"text":"So what will that tell us"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"about the origin of life and the meaning of life?"},{"time":798000,"text":"But perhaps, for me as a chemist,"},{"time":800000,"text":"I want to keep away from general terms;"},{"time":802000,"text":"I want to think about specifics."},{"time":804000,"text":"So what does it mean about defining life?"},{"time":806000,"text":"We really struggle to do this."},{"time":808000,"text":"And I think, if we can make inorganic biology,"},{"time":810000,"text":"and we can make matter become evolvable,"},{"time":813000,"text":"that will in fact define life."},{"time":815000,"text":"I propose to you"},{"time":817000,"text":"that matter that can evolve is alive,"},{"time":820000,"text":"and this gives us the idea of making evolvable matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Just a quick question on timeline."},{"time":836000,"text":"You believe you're going to be successful in this project?"},{"time":838000,"text":"When?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"Lee Cronin: So many people think"},{"time":842000,"text":"that life took millions of years to kick in."},{"time":844000,"text":"We're proposing to do it in just a few hours,"},{"time":847000,"text":"once we've set up"},{"time":849000,"text":"the right chemistry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851000,"text":"CA: And when do you think that will happen?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"LC: Hopefully within the next two years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"CA: That would be a big story."},{"time":858000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":860000,"text":"In your own mind, what do you believe the chances are"},{"time":862000,"text":"that walking around on some other planet"},{"time":864000,"text":"is non-carbon-based life,"},{"time":866000,"text":"walking or oozing or something?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":868000,"text":"LC: I think it's 100 percent."},{"time":870000,"text":"Because the thing is, we are so chauvinistic to biology,"},{"time":873000,"text":"if you take away carbon, there's other things that can happen."},{"time":875000,"text":"So the other thing"},{"time":877000,"text":"that if we were able to create life that's not based on carbon,"},{"time":879000,"text":"maybe we can tell NASA what really to look for."},{"time":882000,"text":"Don't go and look for carbon, go and look for evolvable stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885000,"text":"CA: Lee Cronin, good luck. (LC: Thank you very much.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}